.SH "Detailed Description"
.PP 
This interface offers ways to retrieve topology information about OpenGL displays\&.

.PP
Only the NVIDIA display locality information is currently available, using the NV-CONTROL X11 extension and the NVCtrl library\&. 
.SH "Function Documentation"
.PP 
.SS "int hwloc_gl_get_display_by_osdev (\fBhwloc_topology_t\fP topology, \fBhwloc_obj_t\fP osdev, unsigned * port, unsigned * device)\fR [inline]\fP"

.PP
Get the OpenGL display port and device corresponding to the given hwloc OS object\&. Retrieves the OpenGL display port (server) in \fRport\fP and device (screen) in \fRscreen\fP that correspond to the given hwloc OS device object\&.

.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
0 on success\&. 

.PP
-1 if none could be found\&.
.RE
.PP
The topology \fRtopology\fP does not necessarily have to match the current machine\&. For instance the topology may be an XML import of a remote host\&. I/O devices detection and the GL component must be enabled in the topology\&. 
.SS "\fBhwloc_obj_t\fP hwloc_gl_get_display_osdev_by_name (\fBhwloc_topology_t\fP topology, const char * name)\fR [inline]\fP"

.PP
Get the hwloc OS device object corresponding to the OpenGL display given by name\&. 
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
The hwloc OS device object describing the OpenGL display whose name is \fRname\fP, built as ":port\&.device" such as ":0\&.0" \&. 

.PP
\fRNULL\fP if none could be found\&.
.RE
.PP
The topology \fRtopology\fP does not necessarily have to match the current machine\&. For instance the topology may be an XML import of a remote host\&. I/O devices detection and the GL component must be enabled in the topology\&.

.PP
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
The corresponding PCI device object can be obtained by looking at the OS device parent object (unless PCI devices are filtered out)\&. 
.RE
.PP

.SS "\fBhwloc_obj_t\fP hwloc_gl_get_display_osdev_by_port_device (\fBhwloc_topology_t\fP topology, unsigned port, unsigned device)\fR [inline]\fP"

.PP
Get the hwloc OS device object corresponding to the OpenGL display given by port and device index\&. 
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
The hwloc OS device object describing the OpenGL display whose port (server) is \fRport\fP and device (screen) is \fRdevice\fP\&. 

.PP
\fRNULL\fP if none could be found\&.
.RE
.PP
The topology \fRtopology\fP does not necessarily have to match the current machine\&. For instance the topology may be an XML import of a remote host\&. I/O devices detection and the GL component must be enabled in the topology\&.

.PP
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
The corresponding PCI device object can be obtained by looking at the OS device parent object (unless PCI devices are filtered out)\&. 
.RE
.PP

